title: Welcome to Zombozo-Zone!
description: During medieval times, Team Tennyson must fight to remember that they're not in the past at all, but actually at a Renaissance-esque faire, where "King Zombozo" has hypnotized its guests into thinking they live in the past!

title: How to Draw Grey Matter
description: Ben 10 character designer, Chap Yaep, shows you how to draw Grey Matter.

title: Diamondhead AW1: Great Petropian Civil War Part 1
description: Petropia is a planet as breathtaking and indestructible as its crystalline inhabitants, the Petropians. Occupied by many factions, a civil war broke out between the Petropians and the war-like Subsapiens from below. Little did they know, a third faction, the Antrosapians, awaited with far more sinister intentions for the kingdom.

title: Shhh!
description: While chilling at a monastery with a no-noise policy, Ben can't keep quiet and accidentally awakens a dangerous Dragon hidden in a secret chamber below the hallowed halls. A job that might be too much for even Diamondhead to handle.

title: Out to Launch
description: While on a visit to Cape Canaveral, the Tennyson Trio are present for the inaugural launch of an experimental space plane. When Vilgax commandeers the ship, Ben must stop the baddie from weaponizing the shuttle before the countdown hits zero.

title: Past Aliens Present
description: After Ben stumbles upon a video of Cannonbolt ripping up a computer lab on the internet, Team Tennyson must race to State U to find the imposter; but once Ben discovers it is a steam-punk version of his alien that is terrorizing the campus, Ben must take down the man behind the machine, Steam Smythe!

title: Animo Farm
description: Ben stumbles into Dr. Animo's secret lab now ruled by his superior mutants, the Alphas, and must help the lesser animals escape while stuck as Stinkfly.

title: Clown College
description: While tailgating at a State U. homecoming football game, Ben teams up with Grandpa Max's old college buddies to keep the crazy clown Zombozo from robbing the stadium blind at halftime.

title: The 11th Alien Part 2
description: After discovering that Vilgax has joined forces with the Weatherheads to trick him into turning over the Omnitrix, Ben must not only overcome his doubts, but fully embrace his new powers if he is to beat his foes.

title: Reststop Roustabout
description: With the Rustbucket stopped on the Midwest roadside, Ben locks himself inside with his tablet as Max and Gwen enjoy the great outdoors, until Team Tennyson is pulled into a wild Jack-a-Lope chase.

title: The Sound and the Furry
description: As Team Tennyson leaves the Frozen Man Festival, Lord Decibel takes center stage to threaten the festival-goers, creating an avalanche if his ransom isn't paid. An over matched Ben must step out of his comfort zone to save the festival from his noisy nemesis!

title: Need for Speed
description: Touring Yellowstone, Ben uncovers a plot by the fast & furious LaGrange to find treasure buried below the national park, but with a little help from Old Faithful, Overflow is able to douse LaGrange's dreams.

title: Grey Matter AW2: Lights Out!
description: A reliable power supply is vital to the Galvans' around-the-clock research, so when disaster strikes, or more specifically energy-sapping parasites, these brainy beings must have an even more reliable backup plan for keeping the lights on.

title: Omni-Tricked
description: Ben's vacation to Portland is cut short when he discovers an 11th alien while battling a Dr. Animo Mega-Creature. But when the fight leaves his Omnitrix on the fritz cycling through all 11 aliens, Max seeks help from an old friend to fix the Omnitrix as other dangerous forces seek it including a mysterious alien that's the same species as the 11th alien, Vilgax!

title: Omni-Copped
description: When Grandpa Max's engineer buddy Phil Billings gifts Team Tennyson the Omni-Copter, a state of the art flying vehicle that can transport the Rustbucket for overseas adventures, Steam Smythe takes to the skies to ground Ben and company's first test flight; but unbeknownst to our heroes, Smythe was sent to battle Ben's latest alien forms by a mysterious, powerful enemy: the Forever Knight.

title: Diamondhead AW2: Great Petropian Civil War Part  2
description: The Petrosapien Civil War comes to a crucial turning point as the crystalline Petrosapiens make the hard choice to team up with their warring sub-surface cousins, the Subsapiens, to defeat the monstrous Antrosapiens that dwell near Petropia's dark planetary core.

title: Overflow Special
description: Watch the best videos featuring Ben transforming into Overflow starting with Ben uncovering a plot by the fast & furious LaGrange to find treasure buried below Yellowstone National Park. Also, learn more about Overflow's Planet and how to draw this aquatic alien.

title: Upgrade AW1: Crisis on Galvan B
description: Once devoid of natural life, Galvan B. was upgraded seemingly overnight after a Galvan terraform experiment accidentally crashed into the moon's surface. Relive the birth of the Galvanic Mechamorphs as they rise from the impact site and terraform their surroundings into the lush techno-organic moon we see today.

title: Hole in 10
description: While mini-golfing, Ben is attacked by the Ground Hawgs, a gang of Dr. Animo mutants turned bikers. When the Hawgs realize the faux mini-golf village isn't an actual town, Ben must go alien to stop them before they set their sights on the real city down the road.

title: The 11th Alien Part 1
description: With new Omni-Enhancements in tow, Ben looks to save a town from a sudden mudslide, but his heroics are short lived once Vilgax appears to warn our hero about the consequences of the Omnitrix's mysterious new alien.

title: Safari Sa'Bad
description: On their trip to Adrenaworld West, Ben takes a detour on a jungle cruise and finds himself hunted by the evil Tim Buktu. Our hero must outwit the baddie if he wants to make it off the amusement park ride alive!

title: Mutiny for the Bounty
description: While Phil and Grandpa Max tune-up the Omni-Copter, a restless Ben takes the Rustbuggy off road, but when he is suddenly captured by Textrax and the hunter takes the bounty for himself, our hero must not only escape but avoid the wrath of the double-crossed Kraab and Sixsix!

title: Zombozo-Land
description: Ben, Gwen and Max revisit their favorite amusement park, renovated and re-branded as AdrenaWORLD! Unfortunately, the new management is Zombozo and his trio of new henchmen! He's got a plan to hypnotize everyone in the park to form a criminal army. Ben has to set aside his desire to ride every ride in the park and make things right.

title: Xingo
description: Ben is more interested in a marathon of his favorite cartoon show, "Xingo", but when Ben goes Upgrade to get a better signal, the titular Xingo leaps from his animated dimension to ours, bringing mad chaos with him!

title: Innervasion Part 3: Strange Bedfellows
description: After the Junkbot shoots the Omnitrix and it begins glowing neon-blue, an imprisoned Vilgax explains it is now a gateway through which the Fulmini Empire will invade Earth, but the only way to stop them is from within the Omnitrix, so Ben must team up with the ultimate baddie if he is to save his planet.

title: Charm School's Out
description: During a family cookout at a forest campsite, Charmcaster users her magic to switch places with Gwen, but when Ben catches "Charmcaster" sneaking about, he attacks, unaware it's actually his cursed cousin!

title: Villain Time
description: Ben must go alien to save the Hoover Dam from disaster, but when tough guy hero Tim Buktu swoops in to "help", Ben must figure out if Tim is friend… or foe.

title: Waterfilter
description: Ben, Gwen, and Max's trip to Niagara Falls is cut short by the horrid Hydromanders, creatures menacing them and their fellow tourists.

title: Half-Sies
description: During a trip to the Lake of the Ozarks, Ben and Gwen squabble over Ben's unnecessary "half-birthday" celebration, but when Max gets word of a suspicious rockslide nearby, the cousins must put aside their differences if they are to rescue the trapped miners and uncover who is behind the manmade catastrophe before it's too late: the Bugg Brothers.

title: Ben 24hrs
description: When Ben (and Gwen!) attempt to stay up all night for Adrenaland, the only theme park open 24/7, he not only fails to utilize his alien powers to stay awake, but his "sleep-alien-ing" causes disaster after disaster that Gwen must fix before things get way out of hand.

title: Double Hex
description: While bird watching at Pinnacles National Park, Gwen and Ben get into a competition of who can spot more birds first, but once a forest fire interrupts their fun, Team Tennyson must hurry if they are to save the bird population and discover who is behind the suspiciously growing fire: Hex!

title: Vote Zombozo!
description: When the Rustbucket must tune-up in the same town as Zombozo's latest campaign trail stop, Ben soon discovers the clown is using his speeches to hypnotize then rob the town, and Team Tennyson must stop the baddie from winning the election.

title: Buggy Out
description: After winning a Sumo Slammers Champion belt, Ben returns to the Rustbucket to find his prize in the arms of Kevin, but when his rival hijacks the Rustbuggy instead, our hero must stop at nothing to get back what's rightfully his!

title: Brief Career of Lucky Girl
description: When a wizard cos player gets his hands on a real, magical wand at Comic Con, Ben enlists Gwen to help stop Hex from retrieving it by tricking the wicked warlock into thinking she is a powerful magic-wielder in her own right: the one and only Lucky Girl!

title: XLR8 AW2: Speed Round
description: The Kinecelerans live life at the fastest pace possible, even when they're letting off steam— hence their supercharged take on what we Earthlings call hockey, where every point is more electrifying than the last!

title: Steam is the Word
description: In the heart of Silicon Valley, Ben has to stop Victorian villain Steam Smythe from securing an epic power source sealed in a Tesla time capsule.

title: Mayhem in Mascot
description: After their attempt to get a photo with every storefront mascot is foiled, Ben and Gwen sneak out at night to get their photo with the wooden bear totem known as "Yawk", only to find he and the other mascots have come to life!

title: Innervasion Part 4: Mind over Alien Matter
description: While inside the Omnitrix, Ben and Vilgax must work together if they are to close the gateway, but once the Fulmini leader, the High Override, appears, even that might not be enough. Luckily, help arrives in the form of a being calling itself Glitch!

title: Show Don't Tell
description: Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max arrive at a Native American national park to witness the Ayasha Plinths, an ancient Stonehenge-like rock formation. But when the sinister sorcerer Hex arrives, Ben must battle against a beast Hex magically made out of huge rocks!

title: Poles Apart
description: A trip to the South Pole goes upside down when Team Tennyson lands on the North Pole instead, but Ben quickly discovers the culprits: Solar & Polar Twain, magnetically-powered scientists who want to hold the world ransom by threatening to reverse Earth's magnetic poles!

title: Ben Again and Again
description: After Billy Billions' efforts to carve his face onto Mount Rushmore with a laser are thwarted by Ben, the billionaire brat turns his focus on removing Ben from the Omnitrix, but once he accidentally rips open a rift in space-time, the two must carefully navigate another timeline if they are to return to the present.

title: Adventures in Babysitting
description: Ben, Gwen, and Max meet a family that appears to be a mirror image of them, but when Max goes off on a hike with their matriarch, Maxine, Ben is forced to babysit Simon Sez, a brat with a Billy Billions designed backpack  that turns him into a formidable robot.

title: Baby Buktu
description: When attacked in the jungle, Team Tennyson is saved by a toddler who looks eerily similar to Tim Buktu, but when they discover it really is a pint sized version of the nefarious globetrotter, Ben knows there's another threat looming, Nanny Nightmare!

title: Recipe for Disaster
description: During Chefapalooza in the Rocky Mountains, three famous chefs and infamous bad-guys, The Tri-Chefta, hunt down Wildvine in hopes of creating their most exotic dish to date.

title: All Koiled Up
description: When Ben grows impatient with the snail like pace of gardening, he goes O-E Overflow to pick up the pace and accidentally floods the community garden, but once a giant sink hole appears and frees King Koil and his Kimodo Dragon from below, Ben must quickly right his wrong and capture the baddies if he is to save the coastal city of Bayburgh.

title: Them's Fightin' Words!
description: After enjoying some local corn, Team Tennyson discovers a Hartfield-McJoy reenactment in the cornfield next door, but when Hex resurrects the ghosts of the real feuding families, Ben must find a way to bring them together if he is to save the day!

title: Assault on Pancake Palace
description: When Gwen enters a pancake eating contest at the world famous Pancake Palace, Ben finds the Bugg Bros. and must stop them before they obtain an endless supply of what fuels their creations: Pancake Palace pancakes.

title: Story, Bored
description: During a book signing at a medieval castle, Ben must stop Hex from getting his hands on a grimoire that can fuse its user with mythical beasts, creating monstrous hybrids!

title: Four by Four
description: During their visit to Twin City, Ben and Gwen sign up for some Laser Town awesomeness, but when Ben is teamed up with Kevin, the two must overcome their differences if they are to end up on top!

title: All Wet
description: No one believes Ben when he insists that one of the other patrons waiting in line at the World of Wet Water Park is the nefarious Frightwig disguised as a common girl. So Ben must prove his case while protecting park goers from her master plan: to destroy the park with its own water pressure!

title: Heatblast Special
description: Watch the best videos featuring Ben transforming into Heatblast starting with Ben and Gwen attending an Earth Day concert that gets hijacked by the sound manipulating baddy Lord Decibel! Also, learn more about Heatblast's Planet and how to draw this fiery alien.

title: Wildvine Special
description: Watch the best videos featuring Ben transforming into Wildvine starting with the Rust Bucket running out of gas and Ben, Gwen and Grandpa Max forced to stay at spooky hotel being run by Creepy Carl. Also, learn more about Wildvine's Planet and how to draw this verdurous alien.

title: Stinkfly AW2: The Sweet Smell of Survival
description: For the Lepidopterrans, putting food on the family table is never as simple as running out to the grocery store. Watch as their elite Sky Soldiers go mandible-to-mandible with fearsome Tongue Beetles in what's sure to be a hunger game for the ages!

title: The Filth
description: Ben is tasked with cleaning the Rust Bucket. But when he is tricked into letting the villainous and vile Fly Guys steal it, he must chase them down before they create an unstoppable maggot monster with sights firmly set on destroying Las Vegas.

title: Rath of Con
description: Back stateside, Ben can't get into a cat cosplay competition, Top Tail, without a costume of his own; but when he goes Rath, a new cat-like alien with an attitude, Ben's newfound wild side quickly becomes much more than he bargained for.

title: Bright Lights, Black Hearts
description: Ben, Gwen, and Max stop by the graveyard set of Gwen's favorite TV show, The Unalivers, but when Ben discovers its lead, Michael Morningstar, is an energy vampire he goes alien to show the world the real star of the show: Heatblast.

title: Ye Olde Laser Duel
description: As team Tennyson admires the efficiency of a super modern train station, Ben is quick to sniff out one of Steam Smythe's robots holding up the line. Once the fed up villain tricks our hero into accepting a duel, the fate of the Omnitrix hangs in the balance and it's up to Ben to set things right.

title: Upgrade Special
description: Watch the best videos featuring Ben transforming into Upgrade starting with Ben using Upgrade to get a better signal to watch a marathon of his favorite show starring "Spazz". Also, learn more about Upgrade's Planet and how to draw this high-tech alien.

title: Franken-Fight
description: Ben hops into the Rustbuggy for a driving lesson along the sand dunes of Cape Cod, but he takes a freaky switchback turn when the Rustbuggy is mutated into a motor-monster by Bootleg, another alien transformation of Kevin 11, with powers similar to Upgrade!

title: The Beast Inside
description: Ben, Gwen and Max make a return to Max's alma mater but this time it's no homecoming. Dr. Animo has made a scary transformation and found a way to release the very dangerous animal nature of humans, including Max's life-long friend!

title: Riding the Storm Out
description: Ben and Gwen's camping trip is interrupted by the emotionless Weatherheads (Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o) but a malfunctioning Omnitrix firing out a mishmash of aliens may not be the forecast for success.

title: Overflow AW2: Sentries of Cascareau
description: When the Cascan Pirates aren't plundering the depths of Cascareau for buried treasure, they're depositing their spoils into savings accounts at the Fort Knox of the high seas — a bank built atop an ever-drifting island of pontoon boats, guarded by telepathic Cephalopods, its vaults impenetrable to all but the most loyal customers.

title: Billy Bajillions
description: In Aspen, Colorado, Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max are on a hike to find the Forgeti, but when they realize they've stumbled upon Billy Billions own "Winter in July" ski resort, Ben must battle Billy, with an assist from the Forgeti itself.

title: Fear the Fogg
description: As Max attempts to get Ben and Gwen to the Four Corners Monument before sunset, an ominous fog bank engulfs the roadway and forces Max to drive at a snails pace, but once The Fogg comes to life and attacks the Rust Bucket, Team Tennyson must work together if they are to navigate to safety.

title: Super-Villain Team-Up
description: After a lull in alien antics, a restless Ben suggests to Max and Gwen that he might be a better hero if he went solo, but once Vilgax enlists the help of Zombozo to build a giant hypno-mechanism to hypnotize the entire world, Ben must rethink his strategy if he is to defeat the super-villain team-up.

title: Drone On
description: Ben and Gwen are in a highly competitive paper airplane war, but when alien-tech drones bombard the Rustbucket, the cousins must work together to ground the aerial attack and find out who's behind it: the alien conqueror, Vilgax!

title: How to Draw Upgrade
description: Ben 10 character designer, Chase Standley, shows you how to draw Upgrade.

title: Drive You Crazy
description: After the Rust Bucket breaks down at a Mobile Home Park, Ben discovers they've stumbled on to the last leg of the Cali 10 Hundred, an epic, off-road auto race where mad driver Le Grange has returned for revenge against those that disqualified him years ago.

title: Grey Matter AW1: The Archivists
description: Galvan Prime is home to not only the galaxy's greatest minds, but a DNA bank of every alien species in the cosmos, thus ensuring that the planet forever remains the center of DNA research for the entire universe.

title: Bridge Out
description: After an overpass collapses on the highway, Team Tennyson is in a traffic jam along with Simon Sez and family. But when Ben and Simon team up to tackle the gridlock together, Simon only makes matters much, much worse.

title: Stinkfly AW1: The Silent Circle
description: The circle of life on Lepidopterra is a stinky yet harmonious effort for Lepidopterrans. The wildlife - with slime and toxic gas at their disposal - work together to maintain order on the bustling swamp planet.

title: King Koil
description: Ben and Gwen spend the day volunteering at Repto Ranch and come face to face with King Koil, but need to quickly overcome their fear of snakes if they are to rescue the released critters and defeat the slithery baddie.

title: Bounty Ball
description: While Gwen listens to a lecture on the Transcontinental Railroad, Ben sneaks away to the gift shop. But once the Bounty Hunters appear and corner our hero, Gwen must relay the information she learned on the train and use it to their advantage to help Ben escape.

title: Beach Heads
description: After traveling to Tampa Beach, Florida, Team Tennyson hopes to get some much-needed rest & relaxation, but the tempests without a temper, the Weatherheads, have other plans that Ben must thwart: to build a new beach base!

title: Grey Matter Special
description: Watch the best videos featuring Ben transforming into Grey Matter starting with Ben, Gwen, and Max going on a hike in search of a legendary Forgeti, a yeti that makes people forget they ever saw it. Also, learn more about Grey Matter's Planet and how to draw this tiny alien.

title: Xingo's Back
description: Left to entertain himself as Max takes a much deserved nap, Ben stumbles upon a Xingo arcade game and goes OE-Shock Rock to power it up, but when it receives too much juice, Xingo leaps out into the real world and our hero must go toe-to-toe with his favorite cartoon character.

title: Something I Ate
description: Ben, Gwen, and Max go on a tour of the impervious Fort Knox, but when Dr. Animo sicks a hungry ani-mutate on the Fort, Ben must stop it before it gobbles up the nation's monitory standard!

title: Set Me Free Music Video
description: Ballad of a cursed Bear written by Colin Heck.

title: Four Arms AW1: The Overlordess Games
description: Survival is reserved for only the strongest of warriors on Khoros, where Tetramands prove their worth by staving off savage beasts of the wild and going head-to-head inside massive gladiatorial arenas.

title: Chicken Nuggets of Wisdom
description: When Ben and Max get into an argument, Ben goes Heatblast to blow off steam against Max's wishes; but once Dr. Animo spots him and subsequently turns Max into a chicken, it's up to Ben to right his wrong if he is to save his Grandpa and stop Dr. Animo.

title: Cannonbolt AW1: Beach Ballers
description: As the premiere vacation spot of the cosmos, Arburia is not only a sandy paradise but home to the Arburian Pelarotas. Twelve excruciatingly long hours of work and school stand between the spherical species and a day at the beach spent perfecting their cannonball!

title: Creature Feature
description: When Max dozes off before a double feature, Ben and Gwen are left to save the drive-in by themselves as the evil magician Hex brings the movie monster "That" to life, and unleashes him on the unsuspecting moviegoers.

title: Overflow AW1: The Pirates of Cascareau
description: The torrential surface of the water planet Cascareau forces us undersea, but luckily, this is where all the swashbuckling action is! Let's navigate the watery depths as the Cascans fend off fellow pirates & vicious Leviathans on their quest for a bounty of Serpent Glass, the raw material needed to construct their exoskeleton.

title: Wildvine AW2: The Worldtree
description: The Verda World Tree gives life to the entire ecosystem surrounding it, but like any organic matter, this magnificent specimen has a life cycle of its own. That's where the Florauna come in, herding wild Mushroars, gigantic pollen beetles, to fertilize the wilting tree in time for a blooming spring.

title: Innervasion
description: The mysteries of the Omni-Enhancements are solved when Ben battles an alien invasion coming from inside the Omnitrix.

title: High Stress Express
description: During a live feed of the new transcontinental bullet train, La Grange enters the picture to outrace the train, but Ben joins in on the fun and will stop at nothing to come out on top!

title: Heatblast AW1: Extreme Season
description: At its molten core, Pyros is your typical planet-like star and home to the Pyronites. With rocky exteriors capable of handling these extreme conditions, observe our fiery friends as they pass the time by perfecting their pyrokinetic powers while hanging ten on the gnarliest rivers of lava.

title: Shockrock AW2: Fulmanian Conquest
description: For the Fulmini, enough is just never enough. Traveling from planet to planet, draining worlds of their energy, this mighty race of conquerors must siphon energy from other planets in order to keep their own tapped-out planet spinning.

title: Stinkfly Special
description: Watch the best videos featuring Ben transforming into Stinkfly starting with Ben and Geezer Bob battling a bunch of angry garden gnomes. Also, learn more about Stinkfly's Planet and how to draw this soaring alien.

title: Bon Voyage
description: Aboard the SS Pettigrew on its final voyage, Ben must not only battle seasickness but Steam Smythe, who looks to use his mechanical creatures to sink the steamship's modern replacement and the passengers with it!

title: Don't Laze Me, Bro
description: Ben and his arch-enemy Billy Billions clash in a duel for supremacy at the world's largest Laser Tag Park, LASER TOWN. But, when Billy inadvertently ignites a robot rebellion, and the lasers are set from tag to disintegrate, their childish game escalates into a full blown war! The two foes find that they must set aside their petty differences and team up in order to make it out alive, let alone save the day!

title: This One Goes to 11
description: During one last stop by a toy store before Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max's maiden voyage across the Atlantic, Ben runs into an old bully, Kevin 11, who now has new powers. He's able to transform into aliens just like Ben, such as the "bootleg" doppelgänger of Cannonbolt— Wreckingbolt!

title: Bomzobo Lives
description: During a routine trip to the DMV, Max takes a driving test to renew his license, but when a disguised Zombozo hijacks the role of instructor, Ben goes alien to stop the baddie and save their family road trip.

title: How to Draw Four Arms
description: Ben 10 character designer, Chap Yaep, shows you how to draw Four Arms.

title: Max to the Max
description: While Ben, Gwen, and Max hike to a waterfall, the Bugg Brothers are back with a plan to duplicate Diamondhead; but when their cloning ray gun fires on Max instead, multiplying him endlessly, Gwen and Ben must round up all the Maxes while also fighting off the Bugg Brothers.

title: Four Arms Special
description: Watch the best videos featuring Ben transforming into Four Arms starting with Ben attending the annual Big Bacon Pig Parade, where he uncovers a plot by the Bugg Brothers to rob banks! Also, learn more about Four Arms' Planet and how to draw this mighty alien.

title: XLR8 AW1: Gauntlet of Gliders
description: Kinet, a planet dominated by electrical storms, is home to the lightning quick Kinecelerans! To combat the inclement weather, younglings must complete the Running of the Gauntlet, a most epic retrieval of the gliders worn on their feet. Traversing the desolate terrain at high speeds to reach the lair of a Kinet Molluscarx, the young ones must obtain the creature's precious pearl if they are to fulfill this Kineceleran rite of passage.

title: The Chupaca-bro
description: Team Tennyson discovers that a small village's goats are being terrorized by the legendary Chupacabra, but when Ben realizes it's actually Dr. Animo, our hero must thwart the dastardly doctor before he uses the essence of the goats to power up into an unstoppable form!

title: Tomorrow Today
description: When Max drags the kids to see a defunct "House of the Future" built by his childhood idol, Ben discovers Steam Smythe is busy excavating the joint on the search for a powerful device that will allow him to create devastating weapons for his war on progress. Only Max's devotion to his childhood idol and Ben's faith in dreams can save tomorrow... today!

title: Introducing Kevin 11
description: At a local swap meet, Ben instead sets his sights on a Sumo Slammer collectible, but when Kevin takes it for himself, our hero must get it back by overcoming Kevin's secret weapon: an 11th alien!

title: Screamcatcher
description: When a cavity forces Ben to the dentist his day gets even worse when the malevolent magician Hex uses a nearby dream catcher to bring our hero's fears to life and transports them both to a nightmarish dreamscape.

title: Forgeti
description: When Gwen drags Ben along on a hike in search of the legendary Forgeti, a yeti that makes people forget they ever saw it, Ben is dubious. But with Dr. Animo on the trail of the mythical beast as well, what looks like a hoax becomes a hero time adventure for the ages, if Ben can remember it ever happened.

title: That's the Stuff
description: While touring a space museum, Ben's excitement multiplies when he learns that recently discovered space stuff is being examined inside the museum's lab. Once the stuff comes to life and the shape-shifting goo replicates our hero, Ben must look within if he is to stop the case of mistaken identity.

title: Innervasion Part 2: Call the Dream Police
description: After defeating the Warbot and discovering Vilgax inside, Ben's "secret voices" only worsen and begin affecting his sleep, but once Gwen discovers a sleepwalking Ben using missing items from the campsite to create his own massive Junkbot, it is up to Ben to stop his own creation.

title: Four Arms AW2: The Warspear
description: A look at the perilous lengths to which the Tetramands must go in order to forge their formidable Warspears— the weapons that allow them to survive in such a savage wilderness.

title: Can I Keep It?
description: After stumbling upon a cute cat-dog-rabbit creature hybrid, or "Cadobbit," Ben ignores Grandpa Max's advice and sneaks the animal onto the Rustbucket, but is quickly in over his head as Dr. Amino's creation turns on him!

title: Bad Penny
description: Ben is at the annual Big Bacon Pig Parade, but childhood friend Penny Heaven has met the family to ruin Ben's fun with her safety-obsessed self. While dodging Penny's overzealous safety precautions, Ben uncovers a plot by the Bug Brothers to steal helium from the parade balloons to rob banks with! Penny's badgering turns the heist into an accidental kidnapping so Ben must not only stop the robbery but save his least favorite safety monitor in the process.

title: How to Draw Diamondhead
description: Ben 10 character designer, Chap Yaep, shows you how to draw Diamondhead.

title: Diamondhead Special
description: Watch the best videos featuring Ben transforming into Diamondhead starting with Ben and his arch enemy Billy Billions clashing in a duel for supremacy at the world's largest Laser Tag Park - LASER TOWN. Also, learn more about Diamondhead's Planet and how to draw this dynamic alien.

title: The Ring Leader
description: While winning big on a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben gets the idea to win a wrestling match for real until an intimidating wrestler named Iron Kyle decides to make it a true challenge.

title: How to Draw Wildvine
description: Ben 10 character designer, Chase Standley, shows you how to draw Wildvine.

title: Which Watch
description: After a battle with Kevin gets mysteriously cut short, Ben turns his attention to one upping Gwen at Space Camp. But, when his arch-nemesis, Kevin, returns with his sights strangely set on his cousin, our hero must uncover who is really behind it all, Charmcaster!

title: Take 10
description: While trying to film his own indie film, Ben accidentally allows the Bug Gang to go free and when he takes the fight to their hidden lair Ben has to take on their narcissistic leader, the Ant Queen.

title: How to Draw Stinkfly
description: Ben 10 character designer, Chase Standley, shows you how to draw Stinkfly.

title: Animorphosis
description: As the Tennyson trio dig up dinosaur fossils in the Badlands, Ben is unaware that Vilgax and Dr. Amino have teamed up to steal alien DNA from within the Omnitrix, but once extracted, Vilgax double crosses his fellow villain. Ben must now join forces with the evil doctor to have a chance to defeat the big baddie, but can Dr. Amino be trusted?

title: How to Draw Overflow
description: Ben 10 character designer, Chap Yaep, shows you how to draw Overflow.

title: Rustbucket RIP
description: During a tour of historic Oldeville Ben finds a rare Sumo Slammers card, but when Billy Billions comes to claim the same card Ben has to battle Billy's high-tech drones which have hijacked the Rust Bucket!

title: How to Draw XLR8
description: Ben 10 character designer, Chap Yaep, shows you how to draw XLR8.

title: The Clocktopus
description: In a peaceful coastal town, Ben must not only face the archaic antagonist Steam Smythe and his latest creation, the Clocktopus, but also his deepest, darkest fear: Squids!

title: XLR8 Special
description: Watch the best videos featuring Ben transforming into XLR8 starting with Ben, Gwen and Max visiting their favorite amusement park, AdrenaWorld! Unfortunately, the park's new management is Zombozo and his trio of henchmen! Also, learn more about XLR8's Planet and how to draw this speedy alien.

title: The Charm Offensive
description: After Ben gets too much publicity for his alien antics in Fort Knox, a jealous Gwen feels unappreciated and looks to ease her pain with ice cream, but once she is confronted by Charmcaster looking to avenge Michael Morningstar, Gwen must prove to herself she's a worthy member of Team Tennyson if they are to survive.

title: Dreamtime
description: After a series of reoccurring nightmares affect his sleep, Ben refuses to open up to Max and Gwen about what's bothering him, but once they realize Zombozo himself is behind it, Ben must accept Max and Gwen's help if they are going to put a stop to the terror.

title: Freaky Gwen Ben
description: When Ben interferes with malicious magician Hex's quest for the earth-moving Titan Gloves at a swap meet, he inadvertently switches bodies with Gwen forcing him to walk a mile in her shoes… and vice-versa!

title: Heatblast AW2: Cold Snap
description: Join the Pyronites as they ring in the holidays with a special tradition that would make even the most warm-blooded of visitors go crazy from the heat— racing to the top of Mount Helios, an active volcano!

title: The Feels
description: While Max and Gwen revel in the holiday spirit of Winter Wonderland, Ben couldn't be more unamused and focused on the toys, but once the Weatherheads set their sights on Winter Wonderland as their next target, our hero must become one with his emotion if he is to save the town.

title: Buggin' the Buggs
description: Team Tennyson travel to the Chrysalen Institute for some hot yoga and good vibes, only to find that the Bugg Brothers are on vacation, too, but are the sneaky insectoids really on holiday, or just cooking up yet another silly, yet high stakes scheme?

title: Battle at Biggie Box
description: Ben and Billy Billions go head to head over a Sumo Slammer Set sold exclusively inside the world's largest shopping center, only to find six-year-old Simon Sez has gotten it first! A battle royal ensues inside a store that seemingly has everything except an easy to find exit.

title: How to Draw Cannonbolt
description: Ben 10 character designer, Chap Yaep, shows you how to draw Cannonbolt.

title: Wildvine AW1: Wild Siders
description: Flors Verdana, green with vegetation, is as wild and abundant as the Florauna that inhabit it. Let's take a walk on the wild side as the plant-based aliens trade admiring the planet's lush beauty for the dangerous thrill of waking a sleeping giant.

title: Cannonbolt AW2: When Mega-Sharks Attack!
description: Arburia is well-known across the galaxy for its beach season but this year's interplanetary vacationers won't be catching many waves if the Pelarotas can't rid their waters of an unwanted visitor: the Carcharadon, a billion-toothed beast that makes Jaws look like canned tuna!

title: Cutting Corners
description: Ben approaches Geezer Bob about doing a little yard work to earn spending money, but when Ben goes Upgrade to transform the lawnmower into a super fast mowing machine, he accidentally draws the ire of Bob's gnome-neighbors, the tiny, terrifyingly tenacious Billy-Bob Goblins.

title: Scared Silly
description: When the Rust Bucket runs out of gas on a foggy East Coast road, Ben, Gwen and Max are forced to stay at a hotel being menaced by Creepy Carl, a local folklore expert, who may actually be a ghost!

title: Don't Let the Bass Drop
description: Ben and Gwen are excited to attend an Earth Day EDM concert in Portland until the show is hijacked by the sound-manipulating baddy Lord Decibel who uses sound as a weapon to trash the planet.

title: Innervasion Part 1: Message in a Boxcar
description: As Team Tennyson prepares their boxcar for an upcoming race, Ben is hearing voices and is unable to go Upgrade to enhance his car, but once the race is interrupted by a mysterious Warbot, Ben must overcome the voices inside his head if he is to defeat the giant adversary.

title: Growing Pains
description: During a stop at the superstore Shoppë, Ben and Gwen are transformed into babies by nanny-gone-nuts Nanny Nightmare, who will stop at nothing to reshape the world in the image of her daycare.

title: Cannonbolt Special
description: Watch the best videos featuring Ben transforming into Cannonbolt starting with Ben, Gwen and Grandpa Max hiking to a waterfall and encountering the Bugg Brothers and their cloning ray gun. Also, learn more about Cannonbolt's Planet and how to draw this explosive alien.

title: The Nature of Things
description: While sightseeing at the Geyser Gulch National Park, the Tennyson trio uncover Steam Smythe's steam-powered generator and must shut it down before it overloads the power grid or, even worse, causes a massive earthquake that destroys the entire park!
